description: The Torrente Farfa is a small stream in central Italy. It is located in the Province of Rieti in Italy and flows through the Sabine Hills en route to its confluence with the Tiber River. The valley has been a protected nature reserve since 1979. The Latin poet Ovid refers directly to the river using its Latin name (Farfarus).
